{"word":"εὐλογέω","slug":"εὐλογέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐλογέω</b></el> <el>(εὐλογέω,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to speak well of, praise, honour</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <el>δίκαια εὐλ. τινα</el> <i>to praise</i> him justly, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be honoured</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to bless</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}